Sentencas: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0 Fe-2(0) O-8(3-delta) (LSCF) cathode for solid oxide fuel cells operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere are investigated.
Titulo: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere

Sentencas: LSCF shows different stability against CO2 and H2O at high and low temperature.
Titulo: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere

Sentencas: LSCF has excellent electrochemical performance and high stability against the corrosion of CO2 and H2O at 750 degrees C due to weak reactivity of LSCF with CO2.
Titulo: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere

Sentencas: LSCF shows a serious degradation at 600 degrees C under operation with O-2-CO2(2.83%)-H2O(2.64%), which is ascribed to the impeded oxygen activation and oxygen surface diffusion by surface carbonates and SrCO3 phases on LSCF surface.
Titulo: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere

Sentencas: Under CO2(5%)-H2O(2.81%)-He, LSCF reacts with CO2 to yield SrCO3 phases in 400-680 degrees C, and H2O aggravates the chemical reaction between CO2 and LSCF.
Titulo: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere

Sentencas: Taking into account of SrCO3 phase formation on LSCF, LSCF cathode is stable under operation with O-2-CO2(2.83%)-H2O(2.64%) in 680-800 degrees C, whereas it is unstable below 680 degrees C. LSCF can be subject to degradation caused by CO2 and H2O in air during long-term operation below 680 degrees
Titulo: High- and low- temperature behaviors of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode operating under CO2/H2O-containing atmosphere
